r environment/system property is required. org.apache.activemq:artemis-commons is a utility jar whose needed compile dependencies are resolved transitively; the reported javac failure is stale Base64 API usage in the existing test, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No workflow-level environment variables or system properties are required. For 2.38.0, Base64 exposes encodeObject(Serializable), encodeBytes(byte[], boolean), and decode(String, boolean); do not use removed members such as Base64.DONT_BREAK_LINES or decodeToObject(String). If tests cover FactoryFinder, ClassloadingUtil, or XmlProvider, create ordinary test resources as needed rather than adding workflow setup.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Some optional utility paths read properties such as artemis.default.sensitive.string.codec.key or artemis.disableXxe, but meaningful coverage is reachable without setting them globally.\",\n    \"Avoid exercising full broker/client scenarios; artemis-commons should be tested as standalone utility code, not with an Artemis server container.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0367df76c9e6b7b7016a3f1a4d22cc8193b5fde73a540d9ead\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4026, "output": 984, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32146, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782520387379, "responseId": "resp_0367df76c9e6b7b7016a3f1a43d5708193b5263e36e9d18348"}}
